records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 11 days, Huber privileges for work, school. IMPOSED and STAYED. The Court placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 year.   Court approved participation in the Dosage Probation Pilot Program and probation may be terminated early if the defendant successfully completes the program and all other conditions of probation.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-No violations of State or Federal law that rise to the level of probable cause
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any counseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications
-Work or school part time
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification course
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be paid by 7/27/16; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay related surcharge by 7/27/16; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
The Court finds the defendant is eligible for expunction.
